method.value:
Make crust:
1. Grease a 6cm-deep, 20cm-round (base) springform pan.
2. Process biscuits until mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs.
3. Add butter. Process until just combined.
4. Press mixture over base and side of prepared pan.

Make topping:
1. Stir blueberry spread in low heat until melted.

Make filling:
1. Using electric mixer, beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl until until smooth.
2. Add sour cream.
3. Add eggs 1 at a time.
4. Sift the flour.
5. Pour the filling on top of the base
6. Bake cheesecake in 170C for 1 hours, the cake is slightly puffed and golden brown.
7. Refrigerate until cold.
8. Smooth top with the topping over the cheesecake.

description.value: Delicious easy to make blueberry cheesecake for all occasions.

ingredients.value:
For crust:
80g digestive biscuits
40g butter, melted

For topping:
1/3 blueberry spread

For filling:
250g Philadelphia cheese block, softened
2 large eggs
40g sugar
15g all purpose flour
100g sour cream

method.value:

  2. Add onion and garlic and saute for 3-4 minutes until tender.
  3. Add the peas and saute a minute more.
  4. Pour in the stock and simmer for 3-4 minutes until the peas are just tender.
  5. Blend the mixture until smooth. Add a litte more water if you prefer a thinner soup.
  6. Serve with bay leaf and a swirl of creme fraiche.

description.value: A simple pea soup makes an elegant start to a spring meal. It's also a great way to use frozen vegetables when the produce section is looking bleak.

150 gm creme fraiche

1. Peel and chop the medium mango. Use a blender to puree the mango pieces until smooth.
  2. Beat the cream cheese in a bowl until smooth with an electric mixer on low speed.
  3. Add in the heavy cream, powdered sugar and gelatin. Beat the mixture on medium speed until it thickens.

  2. Heat the wok over high heat.

  6. Add soy sauce and sesame oil and stir fry for another 3 minutes.
  7. Sprinkle with chopped spring onions and serve.

  2. Heat the chocolate and cream in a microwave for 2 to 3 minutes on 50% power, stirring every minute.

  4. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 3 hours until firm.

1. Preheat oven to 200°C.
  2. Line a 12 hole muffin tray with muffin cases.
  3. Sift the self raising flour into a large bowl. Add sugar and stir together to form a dry mixture.
  4. In a separate bowl, whisk egg, milk and vegetable oil together to form a liquid mixture.
  5. Gently pour the liquid mixture into the bowl of dry mixture. Stir with a spoon until slightly lumpy, without over-mixing.
  6. Evenly fold in blueberries.
  7. Divide mixture evenly into the muffin cases and sprinkle sugar on top.
  8. Bake for 25 minutes until lightly golden.
  9. Allow to cool for 5 minutes in muffin tray, before transferring to wire rack.

method.value:
1. Take the steak from the packet and dry it out with paper towel.
  2. Cover the steak liberally with salt and pepper.
  3. Put the steak in the fridge on a rack for 6 hours to encourage it to dry out. This will enhance the flavour, and the salt will be pulled into the steak.
  4. Heat the flatplate part of your bbq and put the steak on the opposite side, and then close the bbq lid.
  5. Put the ghee in a bowl and leave it in the unheated side of the bbq to melt.
  6. Check the steak every 5 minutes with an instant read thermometer. When it reaches 45 degrees celsius, dump it in the ghee.
  7. Brown the steak up on the flatplate, turning every 10 seconds, and liberally dunking it in the melted ghee.
  8. When it is suitably browned, take the steak off the grill, place on a warmed plate and cover tightly with aluminium foil.
  9. After 10 minutes, it is ready. Serve with roast potatoes, steamed green beans and dijon mustard.

  5. Melt remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and stir a little of the water from pasta that is cooking. Keep warm until spaghetti is ready.

body.value:
At Freshery, we believe in healthy cooking and healthy eating. We are committed to teaching people how to prepare meals that are both nutritious and delicious. We support local growers, and all our suppliers are certified organic, and pesticide and GMO-free.

All our in-store ingredients are, where possible, sourced from local producers. We give preference to organically grown, pesticide-free produce, and our eggs are free-range.

We test-drive all our online recipes. Why not book into one of our cooking classes and see for yourself?

Interested in learning how to cook nutritious but delicious meals that are simple to prepare? Why not sign-up for one of our in-store cooking lessons from our team of friendly and informative chefs?

Like what you see? All the ingredients for our online recipes are available at our store!

method.value:
1. Pour the 6 cups of water in a large saucepan, add salt and boil over medium high heat.
  2. Add squid and cook for 3 minutes until tender. Remove squid with a slotted spoon and drain in ice water. Cut squid into small pieces and place in a large bowl.
  3. Add shrimp to boiling water and cook for 3 minutes until tender. Remove squid with a slotted spoon and drain in ice water. Place squid in the large bowl with squid.
  4. Add octopus to simmering water and simmer for 2 hours until tender. Remove octopus with a slotted spoon and drain in ice water. Cut octopus into small pieces and place in the large bowl.
  5. Add crab stick meat to the bowl of seafood mixture.
  6. Finely chop the fresh herbs.
  7. Add the herbs, olive oil, lemon juice and minced garlic into the seafood bowl. Toss to combine.
  8. Transfer to a plate and serve with lemon wedges as garnish.

description.value: A very quick and versatile pasta-free seafood salad. This is a basic recipe - feel free to add your own spin (grated carrots, diced green or red capsicums, red cabbage, seasonings).

ingredients.value:
6 cups water
1 tsp salt
300g squid, cleaned
300g shrimp, peeled and deveined
300g octopus, cleaned  
300g crab stick meat, chopped
1/4 cup fresh lemon juice
 3 cups mixed fresh herb leaves (mint, basil, parsley)
2 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
2 garlic cloves, minced
Lemon wedges

method.value:
1. In a bowl, mix the pork, egg, flour, cabbage and scallions to make the filling mixture.
  2. Scoop 1tbsp of mixture into the middle of a dumpling sheet. Adjust the amount of filling depending on size of your sheets.
  3. Fold the sheet in half and press the edges together to seal the mixture inside. If you find that the edges don't stick easily, adding a small amount of water or egg yolk to the edge before pressing may help. Repeat until all of the mixture is used up.
  4. Place the dumplings inside a steamer pot and steam for 15 minutes or until the dumpling skin becomes soft and slightly translucent.
  5. To make the dipping sauce, mix the soy sauce, sugar and a few scallion pieces in a small dish. Ensure that the sugar has been completely disolved before serving.
  6. Enjoy!

description.value: Delicious and easy to make pork dumplings.

ingredients.value:
1 egg
200g pork mince
50g all-purpose flour
20g shredded nappa cabbage
Dumpling sheets
2 stalks of scallion, chopped
Water
20ml soy sauce
1tbsp brown sugar

method.value:
1. Heat a medium saucepan of water (enough to cover eggs) to a simmer.
  2. Break eggs into a small dish and gently add into the water.
  3. Cook the eggs for 3-4 minutes.
  4. While the eggs are poaching, toast the slices of bread.
  5. Mash the avocado with some lime juice, salt and pepper.
  6. Spread avocado mixture over each toast and sprinkle with some goat cheese.
  7. Top toasts with spinach and poached egg.

description.value: This easy poached egg and avocado toast takes less than 10 minutes from start to finish! A healthy whole food breakfast to start your day right!

ingredients.value:
2 eggs
2 slices of whole grain bread
1 avocado
1 tbsp shredded goat cheese
Lime wedges
Handful of spinach
Salt and pepper
